<p>
  A spotlight on the ground is shining on a wall <m>$a\text{m}</m> away.
  If a woman <m>2\text{m}</m> tall walks from the spotlight toward the
  building at a speed of <m>$b\text{m/s}</m>, how fast is the length of
  her shadow on the building decreasing when she is <m>$c\text{m}</m>
  from the building?
</p>

<p>
  Answer (in meters per second):
  <answer><award>$ans</award></answer>
</p>

